summary:
Edith Eger &ldquo;Our painful experiences aren&rsquo;t a liability—they&rsquo;re a gift. They give us perspective and meaning, an opportunity to find our unique purpose and our strength.&rdquo;
&ldquo;It&rsquo;s the first time I see that we have a choice: to pay attention to what we&rsquo;ve lost or to pay attention to what we still have.&rdquo; &mdash; Edith Eger, The Choice: Embrace the Possible
Suffering is universal. But victimhood is optional. There is a difference between victimization and victimhood.
